com.datastax.oss.driver.api.core.metadata

Interface Metadata


  • public interface Metadata
    The metadata of the Cassandra cluster that this driver instance is connected to.

    Updates to this object are guaranteed to be atomic: the node list, schema, and token metadata are immutable, and will always be consistent for a given metadata instance. The node instances are the only mutable objects in the hierarchy, and some of their fields will be modified dynamically (in particular the node state).

    See Also:
    Session.getMetadata()

    • Method Detail

      • getNodes

        @NonNull
Map<UUID,Node> getNodes()
        The nodes known to the driver, indexed by their unique identifier (host_id in system.local/system.peers). This might include nodes that are currently viewed as down, or ignored by the load balancing policy.

      • findNode

        @NonNull
default Optional<Node> findNode(@NonNull
                                         EndPoint endPoint)
        Finds the node with the given connection information, if it exists.

        Note that this method performs a linear search of getNodes().

      • findNode

        @NonNull
default Optional<Node> findNode(@NonNull
                                         InetSocketAddress broadcastRpcAddress)
        Finds the node with the given untranslated broadcast RPC address, if it exists.

        Note that this method performs a linear search of getNodes().

      • getKeyspaces

        @NonNull
Map<CqlIdentifier,KeyspaceMetadata> getKeyspaces()
        The keyspaces defined in this cluster.

        Note that schema metadata can be disabled or restricted to a subset of keyspaces, therefore this map might be empty or incomplete.

        See Also:
        DefaultDriverOption.METADATA_SCHEMA_ENABLED, Session.setSchemaMetadataEnabled(Boolean), DefaultDriverOption.METADATA_SCHEMA_REFRESHED_KEYSPACES

      • getKeyspace

                                                        CqlIdentifier keyspaceId)

      • getKeyspace

        @NonNull
default Optional<KeyspaceMetadata> getKeyspace(@NonNull
                                                        String keyspaceName)
        Shortcut for getKeyspace(CqlIdentifier.fromCql(keyspaceName)).

      • getTokenMap

        @NonNull
Optional<TokenMap> getTokenMap()
        The token map for this cluster.

        Note that this property might be absent if token metadata was disabled, or if there was a runtime error while computing the map (this would generate a warning log).

        See Also:
        DefaultDriverOption.METADATA_TOKEN_MAP_ENABLED

      • getClusterName

        @NonNull
default Optional<String> getClusterName()
        The cluster name to which this session is connected. The Optional returned should contain the value from the server for system.local.cluster_name.

        Note that this method has a default implementation for backwards compatibility. It is expected that any implementing classes override this method.
